<TEXT>
   ADVERTISING: New York-based ad agency N W Ayer Inc. agreed to buy 25% of British ad agency Ayer Barker for about $4.7 million. 
The price is subject to adjustments in 1990 based on after-tax profit. 
Ayer also said it plans to purchase an additional 31% of Ayer Barker in 1990. 
Ayer Barker is a unit of British communications firm Charles Barker PLC, a public company in which N W Ayer has a 12.7% stake. 
The purchase doesn't affect Ayer's shareholding in the parent company. 

   WHO'S NEWS: Burson-Marsteller named Terrence Hill executive vice president and director of corporate advertising. 
He was with a division of WPP Group PLC's J. Walter Thompson advertising unit. 

